      • chance

        public float chance
        When instantiated this is the relative chance of this feature being spawned. This is later modified to represent a percentage value relative to all other non-absolute entries.

      • absolute

        public boolean absolute
        If true then chance won't be altered. That does not make it an absolute per-day chance.
        See Also:
        FeatureGenerator.spawn(float, boolean)

      • starting

        public boolean starting
        If true this feature will be eligible for instantiation both during World generation and during normal gameplay. If false will only be spawned during normal gameplay.

      • max

        public java.lang.Integer max
        If not null won't spawn any more of these feature if their maximum allowerd number per World has been reached already.

      • seeds

        public java.lang.Integer seeds
        The starting number of instances of this feature to generate on the world map. Default seed is always at least 1 so that debug statistics won't botch.
